Print a shell completion script for `hh` (FR-6.2 ergonomics).

Writes the completion script for the given shell to stdout. Install it per your shell's conventions (see docs/completions.md). The script is plain text and pipe-safe.

Usage: hh completions <SHELL>

Arguments:
  <SHELL>
          Target shell. One of: bash, zsh, fish, powershell, elvish
          
          [possible values: bash, elvish, fish, powershell, zsh]

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Example:
  hh completions bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/hh
  hh completions zsh > ~/.zsh/_hh
  hh completions fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/hh.fish
  hh completions powershell | Out-String | Invoke-Expression
